# MTX Hosting — Project Rules

You are working on **MTX Hosting**, the managed hosting marketing site for MTX Studio.

## Before generating code
- Read `docs/PRD.md` for scope and pages.
- Read `docs/SKILLS.md` for folder structure, naming, and patterns.
- Read `BRIEF.md` for brand, color, and design intent.

## Hard rules
- Stack: Next.js 15 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS. No other frameworks.
- This is a **static marketing site**. No databases, no auth, no provisioning logic in V1.
- Pricing data lives ONLY in `lib/plans.ts`. Never hardcode prices in components.
- Default to server components; add `"use client"` only when interactivity requires it.
- Tailwind only for styling, using the brand tokens from the Tailwind config — no raw hex in markup, no CSS-in-JS.
- Dark theme only. Brand colors: bg #080c10, accent #00e5ff, accent2 #0077ff, ink #e8edf2, muted #5a6a7a.
- Fonts via `next/font`: Syne (display), DM Mono (mono/labels).

## Quality bar
- Lighthouse 95+. LCP < 1.5s.
- Semantic, accessible HTML (AA contrast, keyboard nav, focus rings).
- Conventional commit messages.

## When unsure
Ask a focused question rather than inventing scope. Keep changes targeted to the request.
